Major triads consist of a minor 3rd on top of a Major 3rd
Minor triads consist of a Major 3rd on top of a minor 3rd
Natural minor scales follow a WholeHalfWWHWW - step pattern
Major scales follow a WholeWholeHalfWWWH - step pattern
The keys of F,Bb,Eb,Ab,Db,Gb and Cb contain between 1 and 7 flats
The keys of G,D,A,E,B,F# and C# contain between 1 and 7 sharps
